My intuition is telling me that the diode trick should work, as I think it
will eliminate extraneous tach signal zero crossings that may be fooling my
tach.
I happen to have some 1N4004 diodes on hand, which are similar to 1N4005
except mine have only 400 PIV, while the 1N4005 has 600 PIV.
I'm guessing it shouldn't matter.
I might get a chance to try this tomorrow.

